Result: false  
Justification: The condition C11 requires that for every minimal semantic basis of the claim, there exists at least one P-type argument whose justification contains that basis. In this case, the claim is "Buster is loving," and the minimal semantic bases are derived from the logical inferences needed to establish it. The S-type arguments provide fragments of support: one argues Buster must be loving (by interpreting "either obedient or playful" as exclusive), and another argues it is uncertain (by interpreting it as inclusive). The P-type arguments similarly reflect these conflicting interpretations. However, there is no single P-type argument whose justification semantically encompasses all minimal bases (both interpretations) to conclusively support the claim. Since the claim's truth depends on an unresolved ambiguity, the condition fails.